{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014zS6EynsDWHr8oxAYB7kCa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WdjEBkd1m9XAsDvc1CZEuv","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/aparkin/BERIL-research-observatory/projects/caulobacter_fur_lipida_loss/talks/draft_1/audit/revisions/F002.revised_slide.json","content":"{\n  \"id\": 4,\n  \"position\": 4,\n  \"substory_id\": null,\n  \"layout\": \"claim_evidence\",\n  \"content\": {\n    \"title\": \"Approach: fitness ranking, transcript/proteome panel, and cross-species annotation screen — five mechanism layers\",\n    \"bullets\": [\n      \"RB-TnSeq fitness ranking across 198 Caulobacter experiments + Leaden 2018 Δ*fur* concordance → operative Fur-released subset (vs 33.25% genome background)\",\n      \"Transcript + proteome panel across 3 strain contrasts → ChvI phase structure, constitutive sphingolipid state, candidate Lpt repurposing (transcript-up, protein discordant), and PG remodel (28 loci)\",\n      \"NCBI annotation screen across *A. baumannii*, *N. meningitidis*, *M. catarrhalis* → structural absence of sphingolipid pathway and ChvG-ChvI confirmed\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"speaker_notes_seed\": \"This Approach slide maps the five mechanism layers the deck will deliver. When presenting bullet 2, flag the Lpt language explicitly: say 'transcript is consistent with Lpt maintenance and possible repurposing — MsbA-like CCNA_00307 and LptC-related CCNA_03716 are both significantly up at the transcript level. However, the two canonical Lpt proteins we actually measured — LptD and LptE — decline in the rescued strain (−0.47 and −0.78 log2 respectively). The data are mixed, so we call this candidate repurposing.' Do not say the Lpt apparatus is maintained or repurposed without the qualifier. The replicated proteomics scheduled for summer 2026 are needed to resolve the transcript-protein discordance. This framing matches the evidence-leveling used on the Layer-3 detail slide and in Q&A appendix slide 32.\",\n  \"evidence_anchors\": [\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Interpretation §5\"},\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 4 protein table\"}\n  ],\n  \"revision_log\": [\n    {\n      \"revised_at\": \"2026-06-07T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"finding_id\": \"F002\",\n      \"finding_class\": \"claim_evidence\",\n      \"summary\": \"Bullet 2 rephrased from 'Lpt repurposing' to 'candidate Lpt repurposing (transcript-up, protein discordant)' so the Approach slide does not over-promise what the body must walk back; matches REPORT §Interpretation §5 MIXED verdict and §Finding 4 protein table (LptD −0.47, LptE −0.78 decline at protein level); speaker notes instruct presenter to lead with the discordance caveat.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1448,"cache_read_input_tokens":45812,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1448},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8c1102ad-e023-4bca-a595-b039373ddb51","uuid":"7c8da0c1-3cdb-4758-b884-c16d87a71185"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WdjEBkd1m9XAsDvc1CZEuv","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/aparkin/BERIL-research-observatory/projects/caulobacter_fur_lipida_loss/talks/draft_1/audit/revisions/F002.revised_slide.json has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8c1102ad-e023-4bca-a595-b039373ddb51","uuid":"dc41deea-752a-4139-b2dd-de5bfd46dfc4","timestamp":"2026-06-07T16:32:41.269Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/home/aparkin/BERIL-research-observatory/projects/caulobacter_fur_lipida_loss/talks/draft_1/audit/revisions/F002.revised_slide.json","content":"{\n  \"id\": 4,\n  \"position\": 4,\n  \"substory_id\": null,\n  \"layout\": \"claim_evidence\",\n  \"content\": {\n    \"title\": \"Approach: fitness ranking, transcript/proteome panel, and cross-species annotation screen — five mechanism layers\",\n    \"bullets\": [\n      \"RB-TnSeq fitness ranking across 198 Caulobacter experiments + Leaden 2018 Δ*fur* concordance → operative Fur-released subset (vs 33.25% genome background)\",\n      \"Transcript + proteome panel across 3 strain contrasts → ChvI phase structure, constitutive sphingolipid state, candidate Lpt repurposing (transcript-up, protein discordant), and PG remodel (28 loci)\",\n      \"NCBI annotation screen across *A. baumannii*, *N. meningitidis*, *M. catarrhalis* → structural absence of sphingolipid pathway and ChvG-ChvI confirmed\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"speaker_notes_seed\": \"This Approach slide maps the five mechanism layers the deck will deliver. When presenting bullet 2, flag the Lpt language explicitly: say 'transcript is consistent with Lpt maintenance and possible repurposing — MsbA-like CCNA_00307 and LptC-related CCNA_03716 are both significantly up at the transcript level. However, the two canonical Lpt proteins we actually measured — LptD and LptE — decline in the rescued strain (−0.47 and −0.78 log2 respectively). The data are mixed, so we call this candidate repurposing.' Do not say the Lpt apparatus is maintained or repurposed without the qualifier. The replicated proteomics scheduled for summer 2026 are needed to resolve the transcript-protein discordance. This framing matches the evidence-leveling used on the Layer-3 detail slide and in Q&A appendix slide 32.\",\n  \"evidence_anchors\": [\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Interpretation §5\"},\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 4 protein table\"}\n  ],\n  \"revision_log\": [\n    {\n      \"revised_at\": \"2026-06-07T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"finding_id\": \"F002\",\n      \"finding_class\": \"claim_evidence\",\n      \"summary\": \"Bullet 2 rephrased from 'Lpt repurposing' to 'candidate Lpt repurposing (transcript-up, protein discordant)' so the Approach slide does not over-promise what the body must walk back; matches REPORT §Interpretation §5 MIXED verdict and §Finding 4 protein table (LptD −0.47, LptE −0.78 decline at protein level); speaker notes instruct presenter to lead with the discordance caveat.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":35,"newStart":1,"newLines":27,"lines":[" {","-  \"id\": 16,","-  \"position\": 16,","-  \"substory_id\": \"S3\",","-  \"layout\": \"data_figure\",","+  \"id\": 4,","+  \"position\": 4,","+  \"substory_id\": null,","+  \"layout\": \"claim_evidence\",","   \"content\": {","-    \"title\": \"Sphingolipid biosynthesis is constitutive: 0 of 6 genes UP; spt and sphk mildly DOWN\",","-    \"figure\": \"figures/NB04_sphingolipid_locus_heatmap.png\",","-    \"caption\": \"Sphingolipid biosynthesis locus expression across strains; spt -0.64 (FDR 0.002), sphk -0.40 (FDR 0.02); 0 of 6 genes significantly upregulated.\",","-    \"data_source\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 4; NB04_sphingolipid_lpt_panel.ipynb cell 3\",","-    \"citations\": [","-      \"Zik2022\",","-      \"OleaOzuna2021\"","+    \"title\": \"Approach: fitness ranking, transcript/proteome panel, and cross-species annotation screen — five mechanism layers\",","+    \"bullets\": [","+      \"RB-TnSeq fitness ranking across 198 Caulobacter experiments + Leaden 2018 Δ*fur* concordance → operative Fur-released subset (vs 33.25% genome background)\",","+      \"Transcript + proteome panel across 3 strain contrasts → ChvI phase structure, constitutive sphingolipid state, candidate Lpt repurposing (transcript-up, protein discordant), and PG remodel (28 loci)\",","+      \"NCBI annotation screen across *A. baumannii*, *N. meningitidis*, *M. catarrhalis* → structural absence of sphingolipid pathway and ChvG-ChvI confirmed\"","     ]","   },","-  \"speaker_notes_seed\": \"When this heatmap appears, the headline result is immediate: the sphingolipid biosynthesis locus is flat to slightly declining across the rescue strain series — not induced.\\n\\nFrom REPORT.md §Finding 4: 0 of 6 sphingolipid biosynthesis genes is significantly upregulated in the 4599-vs-4584 contrast at FDR < 0.05. The two most sensitive readouts — serine palmitoyltransferase spt and sphingosine kinase sphk — are both significantly DOWN: spt logFC −0.64 FDR 0.002, sphk logFC −0.40 FDR 0.02. Both p-values are from the single 4599-vs-4584 contrast designed to isolate the Δlpxc-specific response. These are among the few genome-wide significant hits in the biosynthesis panel, and they go in the wrong direction for any emergency induction model. The REPORT scorecard records this as \\\"PASS strongly\\\" for the constitutive sub-claim.\\n\\nThe biology encoded here is the central mechanistic claim of Layer 3. The cell does not respond to losing lipid A by making more CPG biosynthesis transcript. The existing CPG pool — constitutive, present in wild type — is what sustains the outer-membrane substitution. This rules out the simplest emergency-response framing. Zik 2022 showed CPG is required for Δlpxc viability; this layer shows CPG supply is constitutive, not demand-responsive. Olea-Ozuna 2021 established the five structural genes required for ceramide synthesis in Caulobacter and for bacterial survival — those genes are in this locus, and none are induced here. Substitution is flux-driven, not transcriptionally programmed.\\n\\nOne critical caveat must land in delivery: we tested transcript-level regulation only. Post-transcriptional mechanisms — enzyme stabilization, allosteric flux redistribution, or substrate competition relief when LPS synthesis stops consuming shared precursors — are not excluded by these data. The constitutive-transcript finding forecloses transcriptional induction; it does not foreclose post-translational flux routing through the existing biosynthetic machinery. The audience should leave this slide knowing the CPG pool is always-on, not knowing the full flux story. The next slide turns to whether the Lpt transport apparatus is maintained to ship that standing pool across the periplasm to the outer leaflet.\",","+  \"speaker_notes_seed\": \"This Approach slide maps the five mechanism layers the deck will deliver. When presenting bullet 2, flag the Lpt language explicitly: say 'transcript is consistent with Lpt maintenance and possible repurposing — MsbA-like CCNA_00307 and LptC-related CCNA_03716 are both significantly up at the transcript level. However, the two canonical Lpt proteins we actually measured — LptD and LptE — decline in the rescued strain (−0.47 and −0.78 log2 respectively). The data are mixed, so we call this candidate repurposing.' Do not say the Lpt apparatus is maintained or repurposed without the qualifier. The replicated proteomics scheduled for summer 2026 are needed to resolve the transcript-protein discordance. This framing matches the evidence-leveling used on the Layer-3 detail slide and in Q&A appendix slide 32.\",","   \"evidence_anchors\": [","-    {","-      \"kind\": \"report_section\",","-      \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 4 (table row: sphingolipid biosynthesis constitutive)\"","-    },","-    {","-      \"kind\": \"report_section\",","-      \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §NB04 figure inventory (line 141): figures/NB04_sphingolipid_locus_heatmap.png\"","-    }","+    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Interpretation §5\"},","+    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 4 protein table\"}","   ],","   \"revision_log\": [","     {","       \"revised_at\": \"2026-06-07T00:00:00Z\",","       \"finding_id\": \"F002\",","       \"finding_class\": \"claim_evidence\",","-      \"summary\": \"Swapped figure from figures/00_sphingolipid_locus_heatmap.png (NB00 orientation heatmap, CPM-normalized, not FDR-tested) to figures/NB04_sphingolipid_locus_heatmap.png (NB04 DE-tested cluster heatmap) so the caption's FDR statistics (spt FDR 0.002; sphk FDR 0.02) are evidenced by the FDR-tested figure. All other content unchanged; caption and data_source were already correctly grounded in REPORT.md §Finding 4.\"","+      \"summary\": \"Bullet 2 rephrased from 'Lpt repurposing' to 'candidate Lpt repurposing (transcript-up, protein discordant)' so the Approach slide does not over-promise what the body must walk back; matches REPORT §Interpretation §5 MIXED verdict and §Finding 4 protein table (LptD −0.47, LptE −0.78 decline at protein level); speaker notes instruct presenter to lead with the discordance caveat.\"","     }","   ]"," }"]}],"originalFile":"{\n  \"id\": 16,\n  \"position\": 16,\n  \"substory_id\": \"S3\",\n  \"layout\": \"data_figure\",\n  \"content\": {\n    \"title\": \"Sphingolipid biosynthesis is constitutive: 0 of 6 genes UP; spt and sphk mildly DOWN\",\n    \"figure\": \"figures/NB04_sphingolipid_locus_heatmap.png\",\n    \"caption\": \"Sphingolipid biosynthesis locus expression across strains; spt -0.64 (FDR 0.002), sphk -0.40 (FDR 0.02); 0 of 6 genes significantly upregulated.\",\n    \"data_source\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 4; NB04_sphingolipid_lpt_panel.ipynb cell 3\",\n    \"citations\": [\n      \"Zik2022\",\n      \"OleaOzuna2021\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"speaker_notes_seed\": \"When this heatmap appears, the headline result is immediate: the sphingolipid biosynthesis locus is flat to slightly declining across the rescue strain series — not induced.\\n\\nFrom REPORT.md §Finding 4: 0 of 6 sphingolipid biosynthesis genes is significantly upregulated in the 4599-vs-4584 contrast at FDR < 0.05. The two most sensitive readouts — serine palmitoyltransferase spt and sphingosine kinase sphk — are both significantly DOWN: spt logFC −0.64 FDR 0.002, sphk logFC −0.40 FDR 0.02. Both p-values are from the single 4599-vs-4584 contrast designed to isolate the Δlpxc-specific response. These are among the few genome-wide significant hits in the biosynthesis panel, and they go in the wrong direction for any emergency induction model. The REPORT scorecard records this as \\\"PASS strongly\\\" for the constitutive sub-claim.\\n\\nThe biology encoded here is the central mechanistic claim of Layer 3. The cell does not respond to losing lipid A by making more CPG biosynthesis transcript. The existing CPG pool — constitutive, present in wild type — is what sustains the outer-membrane substitution. This rules out the simplest emergency-response framing. Zik 2022 showed CPG is required for Δlpxc viability; this layer shows CPG supply is constitutive, not demand-responsive. Olea-Ozuna 2021 established the five structural genes required for ceramide synthesis in Caulobacter and for bacterial survival — those genes are in this locus, and none are induced here. Substitution is flux-driven, not transcriptionally programmed.\\n\\nOne critical caveat must land in delivery: we tested transcript-level regulation only. Post-transcriptional mechanisms — enzyme stabilization, allosteric flux redistribution, or substrate competition relief when LPS synthesis stops consuming shared precursors — are not excluded by these data. The constitutive-transcript finding forecloses transcriptional induction; it does not foreclose post-translational flux routing through the existing biosynthetic machinery. The audience should leave this slide knowing the CPG pool is always-on, not knowing the full flux story. The next slide turns to whether the Lpt transport apparatus is maintained to ship that standing pool across the periplasm to the outer leaflet.\",\n  \"evidence_anchors\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"report_section\",\n      \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 4 (table row: sphingolipid biosynthesis constitutive)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"report_section\",\n      \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §NB04 figure inventory (line 141): figures/NB04_sphingolipid_locus_heatmap.png\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"revision_log\": [\n    {\n      \"revised_at\": \"2026-06-07T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"finding_id\": \"F002\",\n      \"finding_class\": \"claim_evidence\",\n      \"summary\": \"Swapped figure from figures/00_sphingolipid_locus_heatmap.png (NB00 orientation heatmap, CPM-normalized, not FDR-tested) to figures/NB04_sphingolipid_locus_heatmap.png (NB04 DE-tested cluster heatmap) so the caption's FDR statistics (spt FDR 0.002; sphk FDR 0.02) are evidenced by the FDR-tested figure. All other content unchanged; caption and data_source were already correctly grounded in REPORT.md §Finding 4.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n","userModified":false}}
